Package com.adobe.aem.commons.assetshare.configuration

Interface AssetDetailsResolver

  • @ProviderType
public interface AssetDetailsResolver
    This interface binds OSGi Services that in turn resolve the appropriate AssetDetails page for the provided assets.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      default String getFullUrl​(Config config, AssetModel asset)
      Returns the URL to the asset details page used to render the provided asset.
      String getUrl​(Config config, AssetModel asset)
      Returns the URL to the asset details page used to render the provided asset.

    • Method Detail

      • getUrl

        String getUrl​(Config config,
              AssetModel asset)
        Returns the URL to the asset details page used to render the provided asset. It does NOT include the suffix path which points to the asset to load (path or UUID). If the suffix is desired, use the getFullUrl(..) method. Example return values: - /content/my-asset-share/details/image.html - /content/my-asset-share/details/video.html
        Parameters:
        config - the asset share Config object
        asset - the asset (AssetModel) to resolve
        Returns:
        the url to the asset details page, but do NOT include the asset reference in the suffix.

      • getFullUrl

        default String getFullUrl​(Config config,
                          AssetModel asset)
        Returns the URL to the asset details page used to render the provided asset. It does NOT include the suffix path which points to the asset to load (path or UUID). If the suffix is desired, use the getFullUrl(..) method. Example return values: - /content/my-asset-share/details/image.html/content/dam/pictures/cat.png - /content/my-asset-share/details/video.html/content/dam/videos/puppies.mp4
        Parameters:
        config - the asset share Config object
        asset - the asset (AssetModel) to resolve
        Returns:
        the full asset details link including the asset reference as the suffix.
